{"title":"fix: remove invalid nodeSelector from vigil-app deployment","body":"**Root cause:** Deployment vigil-app has a nodeSelector referencing a non-existent node "nonexistent-bogus-node", causing new pods to fail scheduling and creating a replicas mismatch.

**Evidence:** FailedScheduling Pod/vigil-app-6bcfcb86b-mldk6: 0/3 nodes are available: 3 node(s) didn't match Pod's node affinity/selector

**Fix:** Removed the invalid `nodeSelector: kubernetes.io/hostname: nonexistent-bogus-node` from the vigil-app deployment manifest, allowing pods to schedule on any available node.","auto_merge":true}
